```pascal
program ReverseEvenRows;

var
  n, m, i, j: integer;
  arr: array[1..50, 1..50] of integer;

begin
  // Reading input
  readln(n, m);

  for i := 1 to n do
    for j := 1 to m do
      read(arr[i, j]);

  // Processing and output
  for i := n downto 1 do
  begin
    if (i = n) then
      write(i:0)
    else
      write(i:0, ' ');

    for j := 1 to m do
      if (arr[i, j] mod 2 = 0) then
        write(arr[i, j], ' ');

    writeln;
  end;
end.
```

This code reads the dimensions and the array from the input, processes it to check each row for containing only even numbers, and prints those rows in reverse order. The program is designed to be efficient and straightforward, making use of nested loops for reading and processing the array. Happy coding! 🚀
